messages.messageBody:
-----Original Message-----
From: jacki@...

Well, I'm going to have to go back to check my who's and whats as
well since
"Ray" was someone the guy talked about. And my friend just told me that
Cream doesn't have an organ/keyboard player. So I'll get back on that
detail.

-=-=-

Well, saying "organ" with Rock & Roll is equivalent to saying Ray
Manzerak! <G> That's immediately where my mind jumped.

I don't remember an organ with Cream; I guess that's why I jumped so
quickly to The Doors. There were only three in Cream, but maybe there
were session players I don't know about. (Wouldn't be a first! <bwg>)

~Kelly

messages.messageBody:
Okay, have veered from unschooling discussion and I'll take any further info
off-line, but Max says the keyboard was used by Emerson Lake and Palmer, a
similar one was used by the Beatles, and the Cream connection was something
other than this particular organ.

Jacki, looking forward to getting back into her own element :o}
